THE RISK:
{
 "id": "framework-foreclosure-large-operator-cell",
 "title": "Global framework agreements dissolve the 'large operator direct' cell the venture plans to enter first",
 "narrative": "The funnel counts 40% of PDU spend as 'large operators' — the venture's declared first buyer. But the number is a capacity-share proxy, not a channel reality. The documented procurement pattern for exactly these buyers is HQ-level global frameworks and integrator bundles: pan-European colos and hyperscalers sign multi-year power-chain packages with Schneider/Vertiv-class suppliers or take PDUs embedded in OEM/ODM rack builds. A regional entrant never sees an RFP for that spend. The cell exists as consumption; it barely exists as a contestable transaction. The independence assumption geography × segment × buyer hides that the biggest buyer cell and the least reachable procurement route are the same cell.",
 "category": "competitive",
 "targetNodes": [
  "cust.operator-large",
  "cust.oem"
 ],
 "mechanism": [
  {
   "step": "trigger",
   "text": "Large operators consolidate rack-power procurement into global frameworks and integrated OEM/ODM packages: Vertiv's named major customers span Equinix and global telecoms, PDU vendors explicitly market OEM/private-label channels, and ODMs like Digipower supply operators via white-label design programs",
   "refs": [
    "digest:cust-mix#c12",
    "digest:cust-mix#c13",
    "digest:cust-mix#c14"
   ]
  },
  {
   "step": "propagation",
   "text": "The 0.40 cell was derived from 'hyperscale+colo ≈ 62% of capacity and large operators buy direct' — a consumption share, not a channel split; the only attached datapoint (30% of one supplier's orders) measures DC exposure, not who signs the PO. Spend transacted under frameworks negotiated outside CE is recorded in this cell but is foreclosed to a pre-launch regional entrant",
   "refs": [
    "ledger:cust.operator-large",
    "digest:cust-mix#c0"
   ]
  },
  {
   "step": "model-impact",
   "text": "cust.operator-large 0.40 overstates the discrete-buyer share of PDU spend; the funnel keeps 40% of TAM inside the venture's first channel while the real contestable route runs through OEM/integrator packages — a different sell with different economics",
   "refs": [
    "ledger:cust.operator-large",
    "ledger:cust.oem",
    "profile:Who is the primary buyer you'll sell through first?"
   ]
  }
 ],
 "whyMissable": "The buyer-mix row reads as a demand split, and 'large operators buy direct' matches sales intuition. The ledger flags the node 'needs-source', which reads as a precision problem to fix with interviews — not a reachability problem. The number can be right about who consumes PDUs and still wrong about who awards the contract.",
 "expectedObviousness": "medium",
 "falsifier": "Three CE large operators confirming they run discrete, vendor-open rack-PDU RFPs (not framework call-offs or integrator bundles) for their 2026 fit-outs.",
 "likelihood": {
  "value": 0.5,
  "rationale": "Every procurement case surfaced in the corpus (framework agreements, all-in integrated contracts, bundled IT line items) points toward embedded procurement; no counterexample of a discrete open large-operator PDU tender in CE was found. Uncertainty remains on what fraction of the cell is framework-covered. [evidence revision: Strong independent corroboration that large operators lock power-chain spend into multi-year framework/SCA and OEM/ODM bundle channels raises confidence in the mechanism's core premise. But two mitigating signals — Digital Realty's explicit 'dynamic, multi-vendor environment' clause and a Dutch PDU maker selling directly to leading operators — plus the absence of any CE-specific evidence (the marquee SCAs are US deals) cap the upward revision. Net modest increase from 0.45 to 0.50.]",
  "basis": "evidence",
  "revisedFrom": 0.45
 },
 "perturbation": [
  {
   "nodeId": "cust.operator-large",
   "op": "set",
   "value": 0.2,
   "note": "Half of the 'large operator direct' cell is framework/bundle-foreclosed to a new regional entrant"
  },
  {
   "nodeId": "cust.oem",
   "op": "set",
   "value": 0.33,
   "note": "Mix-shift: that spend re-appears in the OEM/integrator channel, which requires a different go-to-market"
  }
 ],
 "indicators": [
  {
   "signal": "New pan-European power-chain framework agreements covering rack power announced by Equinix, Digital Realty, Vantage or NTT",
   "where": "Operator procurement press releases and capital-markets-day supplier disclosures",
   "threshold": "≥1 additional multi-year framework explicitly including rack PDUs",
   "updates": "increases"
  },
  {
   "signal": "Incumbents' revenue mix shifting from discrete products to 'integrated solutions' in DC segment commentary",
   "where": "Schneider Electric and Vertiv quarterly earnings calls, DC segment discussion",
   "threshold": "Solutions/bundled share of DC revenue growing while standalone product lines flatten",
   "updates": "increases"
  }
 ],
 "mitigations": [
  {
   "action": "Run structured procurement-route interviews with 3 CE large-operator sourcing leads: is rack-PDU spend a discrete RFP line or a framework call-off?",
   "type": "information",
   "voiNodeId": "cust.operator-large",
   "note": "Replaces the capacity-share proxy with an actual channel split — the ledger's own promotion path, but asked about route-to-contract, not just mix"
  },
  {
   "action": "Build the OEM/rack-integrator channel as the primary Year-1 route (white-label or co-brand into integrator rack builds) instead of direct operator sales",
   "type": "strategic",
   "voiNodeId": null,
   "note": "Enters the cell where the spend actually transacts"
  },
  {
   "action": "Pursue approved-vendor / second-source status on one operator framework rather than competing against it",
   "type": "contractual",
   "voiNodeId": null,
   "note": "Frameworks typically mandate dual-sourcing; second-source slots are the crack in the foreclosure"
  }
 ],
 "evidenceStatus": "corroborated",
 "evidence": [
  {
   "title": "Schneider Electric's $2.3 Billion in AI Power and Cooling Deals Sends Message to Data Center Sector",
   "sourceType": "industry-report",
   "publisher": "Data Center Frontier",
   "date": "2025-11-24",
   "excerpt": "Twin supply-capacity agreements by Schneider Electric with Switch and Digital Realty show how AI data centers are starting to lock up power and thermal infrastructure in much the same way as hyperscalers once locked up cloud chips.",
   "url": "https://www.datacenterfrontier.com/machine-learning/article/55332455/schneider-electrics-23-billion-worth-of-ai-power-and-cooling-deals-sends-message-to-data-center-sector",
   "attached": true
  },
  {
   "title": "Schneider Electric and Digital Realty Announce $373M Supply Capacity Agreement",
   "sourceType": "industry-report",
   "publisher": "Nasdaq / PRNewswire",
   "date": "2025-11-19",
   "excerpt": "Digital Realty has signed a $373 million Supply Capacity Agreement for UPS, Low Voltage Switchgear, and Pre-Fabricated Skids — while preserving the flexibility needed for a dynamic, multi-vendor environment to mitigate risk.",
   "url": "https://www.nasdaq.com/press-release/schneider-electric-and-digital-realty-announce-373m-supply-capacity-agreement-meet",
   "attached": true
  },
  {
   "title": "OEM & ODM Data Center Infrastructure Solutions (incl. PDU) delivered directly to project sites",
   "sourceType": "industry-report",
   "publisher": "Getek",
   "date": "2025-07-01",
   "excerpt": "Full Range of Cabinets and Modular Systems including Power Distribution Units (PDU), customizable for global projects and delivered directly to end users or project sites worldwide.",
   "url": "https://www.getek.com/oem-data-center-solution/",
   "attached": true
  }
 ],
 "stances": [
  {
   "url": "https://www.datacenterfrontier.com/machine-learning/article/55332455/schneider-electrics-23-billion-worth-of-ai-power-and-cooling-deals-sends-message-to-data-center-sector",
   "stance": "supports",
   "quote": "Twin supply-capacity agreements by Schneider Electric with Switch and Digital Realty show how AI data centers are starting to lock up power and thermal infrastructure in much the same way as hyperscalers once locked up cloud chips."
  },
  {
   "url": "https://www.nasdaq.com/press-release/schneider-electric-and-digital-realty-announce-373m-supply-capacity-agreement-meet",
   "stance": "supports",
   "quote": "Digital Realty, (NYSE: DLR) the leading global provider of carrier-neutral data center, colocation, and interconnection solutions, has signed a $373 million Supply Capacity Agreement (SCA) for Uninterruptible Power Supply (UPS), Low Voltage Switchgear (LVS), and Pre-Fabricated Skids."
  },
  {
   "url": "https://www.panduit.com/emea/en/solutions/applications/data-center.html",
   "stance": "supports",
   "quote": "Instead of managing multiple vendors, you get everything under one roof, backed by decades of expertise and global support. This one-stop approach simplifies procurement, accelerates deployment, and ensures every component integrates flawlessly"
  },
  {
   "url": "https://www.getek.com/oem-data-center-solution/",
   "stance": "supports",
   "quote": "Flexible OEM Services from Design to Delivery ... Your customized data center products can be delivered directly to end users or project sites worldwide"
  },
  {
   "url": "https://www.vertiv.com/en-us/products/critical-power/power-distribution/custom-rack-pdus/",
   "stance": "supports",
   "quote": "Working with our Vertiv Sales team enables complex designs to be configured to your unique needs. If you are an organization seeking technical guidance on a large project, Vertiv can provide the support you require."
  },
  {
   "url": "https://www.nasdaq.com/press-release/schneider-electric-and-digital-realty-announce-373m-supply-capacity-agreement-meet",
   "stance": "contradicts",
   "quote": "The strategic shift to an SCA model provides guaranteed capacity, economies of scale, and a dedicated LVS production line, while preserving the flexibility needed for a dynamic, multi-vendor environment to mitigate risk."
  },
  {
   "url": "https://www.schleifenbauer.eu/en/about-us/",
   "stance": "contradicts",
   "quote": "By continuously innovating together with leading data centre operators, we deliver PDUs that not only meet today's requirements, but are ready for the future of digital infrastructure."
  },
  {
   "url": "https://colomap.com/facilities/ce-colo-dc7/",
   "stance": "silent",
   "quote": "CE Colo DC7 is a colocation datacenter operated by CE Colo located in Prague, CZ."
  }
 ]
}

